      • getTerminalState

        public State getTerminalState()
        Returns a terminal state. This method is necessary because when an episode ends in RLGlue, it does not provide the last state received. However, BURLAP still expects to receive the ending state, so this method returns a special state that indicates a termainal state.
        Returns:
        a special terminal state object.
